Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Trim the root and the dark green leafy part from the @leeks{2}. Halve lengthways then thinly slice. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Pull the @sage{1%bunch} leaves off their stalks (but keep them whole). Finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch}(finely chopped) (stalks and all). Trim the bottom 2cm off of the @asparagus{200%g} and discard. Pop the asparagus on a #baking tray{}, drizzle with oil and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} - set aside.

Heat a #wide bottomed saucepan{} over medium heat (no oil!) Once hot, add the @pine nuts{15%g} and cook, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> Watch them like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Once toasted, remove the nuts to a #bowl{} and pop your pan back on medium high. Add a quarter of your @unsalted butter{30%g} and allow to melt. Once bubbling, add the sage leaves in a single layer and cook them until starting to crisp, ~{1-2%minutes}. Transfer to the bowl with the pine nuts and set aside.

Meanwhile, pour the @water{750%ml} into a #medium saucepan{} on high heat. Add the @vegetable stock powder{2%cubes}, stir to dissolve and reduce the heat to the lowest setting. Pop your wide bottomed pan back on medium high with a drizzle of oil (no need to wash!). Add the leeks and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry until nicely softened, ~{4-5%minutes}, stirring occasionally. Then stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}. Add the @Arborio rice{175%g}, stir and cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once you've cooked your rice for a minute, stir in a ladle of your stock. When the stock has been absorbed by the rice, stir in another ladle of stock. Keep the pan on medium heat and continue stirring in stock, letting it absorb each time. The cooking time should take ~{20-25%minutes} and your risotto is done when your rice is 'al dente' - cooked through but with a tiny bit of firmness left in the middle.

Halfway through the risotto cook time, pop the asparagus on the top shelf of your oven to roast until tender, ~{10-12%minutes}. When your risotto is cooked, remove from the heat and add the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{40%g}, remaining butter, parsley and @Goat's Cheese{125%g} per person. Stir well to make the risotto really creamy. Taste and add more salt and pepper to taste.

Serve the risotto with the asparagus on one side. Crumble the goat's cheese on the other side and finish with the pine nuts and buttery sage sprinkled on top. Enjoy!